        <item>
          <updateDate>2013-04-12T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <actionDate>2013-04-12</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>Trust Returned to the United States Taxpayer Act or the TRUST Act - Denies retirement benefits under the Civil Service Retirement System (CSRS) and the Federal Employees' Retirement System (FERS) to a Member of Congress who is convicted of any crime that is a felony under federal or state law (currently, limited to specified felonies under federal law). </p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2013-05-22T21:02:03Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
    <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText><![CDATA[<pre>By Mr. YOHO:H.R. 1547.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 6, Clause 1, of the U.S. Constitution:``The Senators and Representatives shall receive aCompensation for their Services, to be ascertained by Law,and paid out of the Treasury of the United States.''[Page H1993]</pre>]]></constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
